# Colocated downstream packages with their own upstream git repos.
# Each subdirectory is an independent project (own Cargo workspace,
# own Cargo.lock, own git remote). They live here for convenient
# path-based deps on Blinc crates like:
#
#   blinc_app = { path = "../../crates/blinc_app" }
#
# but are NOT tracked by this repo and NOT part of its Cargo workspace.
/packages/

# License-restricted demo assets. Bundled examples use CC-BY-4.0 or
# more permissive so they can ship with Blinc's open-source
# distribution. CC-BY-NC-SA-4.0 and similar non-commercial licenses
# stay untracked — developers fetch them manually to iterate on
# their local demo, and the relevant demo degrades gracefully when
# the asset directory is missing.
#
# Pattern ignores the directory's contents but keeps `README.md` so
# the install instructions + attribution requirements ship with the
# repo. Gitignore negation only works when the parent directory
# isn't itself ignored, hence the `/*` style.
/examples/blinc_app_examples/examples/assets/3d/cutegirl_g1/*
!/examples/blinc_app_examples/examples/assets/3d/cutegirl_g1/README.md

./claude/